{
  "stem": "24515.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Obviously as a kid, I was very interested in my father's heroic aspects, but to get him to talk about the war was practically impossible.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Look, he was a-- he was a infantry soldier in the front lines, both in Russia and in France.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I can't understand why he wouldn't talk about it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The only story I ever heard about it was that when he got home on leave, and would I guess what he was most craving coming home on leave.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I couldn't guess, and the answer was a glass of water-- fresh, real water.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Even so, I have a letter somewhere in which he wrote to my mother-- they were more or less engaged, I suppose, at that time-- to my mother that he hoped that Germany wouldn't give up, that he was quite ready to go again if necessary, even though what he was getting-- going into was obviously not very nice.",
      "word_count": 63
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "German.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not much literature, as I recall.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There were articles.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We had a beautiful silver besamim box, or the, the spice box, and Shabbat candle holders and various things like that.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not really.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Not for a long while.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Toward the end-- '37 to '38, somewhere around there-- all of a sudden, my mother made Kiddush Friday evenings.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I was able to make contact with the local rabbi, and asked him an awful lot of questions.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he was very sweet, and, and, you know, discussed things with me for hours.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So I suspect you might say we became more obviously religious as time went on.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, it was always seder, of course.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Hanukkah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Naturally, the high holidays, when you went to Synagogue.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
